Title: Object: An ancient obelisk at Matarea, formerly Heliopolis
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 13 in volume I: three men riding horses in the left foreground, passing by a guard who stands in the centre, entering a camp around an obelisk in a field in the right background; after Mayer; published state. 1802 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.13)
